1.speaker: PENGUIN
1.character: どうしたの　パンダ君　溜息なんかついて
1.definition: What's wrong, Panda? Why are you sighing?

2.speaker: PANDA
2.character: バイト行きたくないよ
2.definition: I don't want to go to work.

4.speaker: PANDA
4.character: 本当に何もすることなくて　超退屈なんだもん
4.definition: There's nothing to do, so it's really boring.

5.speaker: PANDA
5.character: 常勤パンダさんとあっち向いてほいとかしても
5.definition: Even when I'm playing "Hey, look over there" with Mr. Full-time Panda,

6.speaker: PANDA
6.character: 十五分ぐらい厭きるし
6.definition: I get tired of it after fifteen minutes.

7.speaker: PENGUIN
7.character: よく十五分もできるね
7.definition: I'm surprised you can even play that for fifteen minutes.

8.speaker: PENGUIN
8.definition: I'd be sick of it after fifteen seconds.

9.speaker: PANDA
9.character: ペンギンさん　時間潰すのって大変だよ
9.definition: It's really hard to kill time, Mr. Penguin.

10.speaker: PANDA
10.character: 仕方ないから　いっぱいお昼寝してたら
10.definition: I didn't have a choice, so I napped a bunch,

11.speaker: PANDA
11.character: 寝違えって　首回らなくなっちゃうし
11.definition: but I slept wrong and got a stiff neck. Even if I eat my snacks really slowly, only a little bit of time passes.

12.speaker: PANDA
12.character: パンダのバイト始めてから　おやつの食べ過ぎで太っちゃった
12.definition: Ever since I started my part-time job as a panda, I've been eating too many snacks and put on some weight.

15.speaker: PENGUIN
15.definition: You really think that's the only reason? Yup. I'm gaining weight because I have a job.

16.speaker: POLAR BEAR
16.character: パンダ君のバイトって　週二日だよね
16.definition: You work at your job twice a week, right? Yup.

17.speaker: PENGUIN
17.character: 週二日で文句言わないでよ
17.definition: Stop complaining about having to work twice a week.

21.speaker: PANDA
21.definition: Maybe I'll make it once a week.

23.speaker: POLAR BEAR
23.character: いいな　僕は仕事忙しくて　もう少し暇になりたい
23.definition: It must be nice. I'm very busy at work. I'd like a little more free time.

25.speaker: POLAR BEAR
25.character: 偶には気分転換したいね
25.definition: I'd like to have a change of pace once in a while.

26.speaker: SASAKO
26.character: お店忙しいですもんね

27.speaker: PANDA
27.character: あ　いいなぁ　忙しいの
27.definition: Jeez, it must be nice to be so busy.

28.speaker: POLAR BEAR
28.character: パンダ君になってゴロゴロしたい
28.definition: I want to be like you, Panda, and just laze around. Come on, you two. You're asking for things you can't have.

29.speaker: PENGUIN
29.character: 笹子さん　何か言ってやってよ
29.definition: You should say something to them, Miss Sasako.

31.speaker: POLAR BEAR
31.character: いい事思いついちゃった
31.definition: I just got a great idea.

33.speaker: POLAR BEAR
33.character: パンダ君　一日だけ入れ替わってみない？
33.definition: Do you want to trade places for a day, Panda? Huh? I'll go to the zoo to work as a panda,

34.speaker: POLAR BEAR
34.character: パンダ君は白熊カフェでマスターするの
34.definition: and you can manage things here at Polar Bear's Café.

35.speaker: PENGUIN
35.character: いやいや　無理でしょ
35.definition: No, no, no, that's a bad idea.

36.speaker: PANDA
36.definition: That's a great idea. You're really cool, Polar Bear. I've wanted to be like you just once.

38.speaker: PANDA
38.definition: You think so? Stop saying weird stuff, Polar Bear.

39.speaker: HANDA
39.character: あ　おはよう　パンダ君

42.speaker: POLAR BEAR
42.character: パンダコーナーってこっちだっけ？
42.definition: Was this the way to the panda corner?

43.speaker: HANDA
43.character: ちょっと待ってよ！白熊君でしょ？
43.definition: W-Wait a minute! You're Polar Bear, aren't you? Oh, you can tell?

44.speaker: POLAR BEAR
44.character: 半田さん　平気平気

45.speaker: POLAR BEAR
45.character: お客さんには熊の区別なんてつかないから
45.definition: The visitors can't tell the difference between different bears.

47.speaker: HANDA
47.character: 白熊君なの　物分りだよ
47.definition: They'll know right away with you, Polar Bear!

49.speaker: KIRINO
49.character: 待ってください　先輩

51.speaker: KIRINO
51.character: 今日は　常勤パンダさんが有給休暇で休みですよ
51.definition: Mr. Full-time Panda is off today on paid leave.

53.speaker: GIRL
53.character: ママ　パンダさんいないよ

54.speaker: HANDA
54.character: 白熊君　パンダ君は？

57.speaker: POLAR BEAR
57.character: 今から呼んでも間に合わないよ
57.definition: Even if I called him now, it'd be too late.

58.speaker: POLAR BEAR
58.definition: Don't worry. Leave it to me.

59.speaker: HANDA
59.character: な…なるべく目立たないように　お願いします
59.definition: T-Try not to make yourself too obvious, please.

61.speaker: RINRIN
61.character: パンダ君　美味しそうな笹が手に入ったから
61.definition: Hey, Panda! I just got some tasty-looking bamboo grass,

62.speaker: RINRIN
62.definition: so I thought I'd bring you some—

64.speaker: PENGUIN
64.character: 気になって見に来ちゃったよ
64.definition: I couldn't stop thinking about it, so I came to look. I'm a panda.

65.speaker: RINRIN
65.character: 何だか熱があるみたいだ
65.definition: I think I may have a fever.

68.speaker: PENGUIN
68.character: やっぱり無理だよ　全然違うよ
68.definition: I knew this was a bad idea! He doesn't look anything like a panda!

70.speaker: GUY
70.character: 何が違くねぇ？長すぎるっていうか　でか過ぎねぇ？
70.definition: Something seems off. He seems too long, or something. Isn't he too big?

71.speaker: GUY2
71.character: でも俺ら生パンダ見るの始めてたし
71.definition: Well, this is the first time we've seen a panda in person,

72.speaker: GUY2
72.definition: so maybe that's what they look like.

74.speaker: GUY
74.character: なんかあのシルエットは白熊じゃねぇ？
74.definition: isn't that a polar bear's silhouette?

78.speaker: GUY2
78.character: ほら　やっぱりパンダだよ

82.speaker: PENGUIN
82.character: 白熊君　グッドジョブ

84.speaker: LADY
84.definition: Excuse me. Yes, I'll be right there!

85.speaker: POLAR BEAR
85.definition: There really is nothing to do at this job.

86.speaker: GUY2
86.character: あんまり動かないなぁ

87.speaker: GUY
87.character: パンダだもん　仕方ないよ
87.definition: That's to be expected, he's a panda.

88.speaker: POLAR BEAR
88.character: おっと　サービス　サービス

89.speaker: POLAR BEAR
89.character: あれ　タイヤでどうやって遊べばいいんだっけ
89.definition: Huh? How exactly do you play with a tire?

91.speaker: GIRL
91.character: パンダさんどうしたの

92.speaker: PENGUIN
92.character: どうしよう　皆怪しんでるよ
92.definition: Oh, no! Everyone's becoming suspicious! Um...

93.speaker: GUY
93.character: おほ　遊んでる　遊んでる

95.speaker: PENGUIN
95.character: もう　白熊君がありえない動きするから
95.definition: No! You're making everyone suspicious by doing unthinkable moves!

96.speaker: GUY
96.character: 生パンダはやっぱ違うなぁ
96.definition: Seeing a panda in person is totally different! Yeah! What?!

98.speaker: POLAR BEAR
98.character: よし　もっとサービスしよう
98.definition: All right, I'll give them even more service.

99.speaker: GUY
99.definition: Whoa! It's a polar bear! Hey.

101.speaker: GUY
101.definition: Whoa! It's a polar bear! Hey.

103.speaker: GUY
103.definition: Whoa! It's a polar bear! Whoa! It's a panda!

105.speaker: PENGUIN
105.character: （パンダ　白熊　パンダ　白熊……）

106.speaker: HANDA
106.character: パンダがいないとまずい
106.definition: The pandas not being here isn't good.

107.speaker: HANDA
107.character: 白熊パンダがばれてもやばすぎる
107.definition: I'll be in trouble if people find out that Polar Bear isn't a panda. Maybe I should get an apology letter ready... Mr. Handa, we've got a problem! It's finally happened! They've found out!

108.speaker: KIRINO
108.character: パンダ君が大人気ですよ
108.definition: Polar Bear panda is a hit! What do I do?! Huh?

110.speaker: GUY
110.character: すげぇー　あの距離を沈めたぞ
110.definition: Amazing! He made it from that distance!

111.speaker: GUY2
111.character: マスタスでられじゃねぇ？
111.definition: He could probably enter the Masters!

112.speaker: POLAR BEAR
112.definition: Thank you. Thank you. You're so amazing, Mr. Panda!

113.speaker: KIRINO
113.character: パンダグッズも飛ぶように売れてます
113.definition: The panda merchandise is selling like crazy!

114.speaker: GUY
114.character: このパンダティシャツください
114.definition: Could I get this panda T-shirt?

115.speaker: LADY
115.character: パンダバッグ三色全部
115.definition: I'd like all three colors of the panda handbags!

116.speaker: POLAR BEAR
116.character: 半田さん　大成功でしょ

117.speaker: PENGUIN
117.character: そういえば　あっちはどうなったかな
117.definition: Now that I think about it, I wonder how it's going on the other end.

120.speaker: MAN
120.character: なにしようかな　えっと
120.definition: I wonder what I should get. Let's see...

121.speaker: MAN2
121.character: いや　その　白熊にしてはちょっと小さいというか
121.definition: Aren't you a little short to be a polar bear? Or rather...

123.speaker: PANDA
123.character: いいえ　白熊ですよ
123.definition: No, I'm Polar Bear. Where did Polar Bear go? I'm right here.
